p:
Mean change in IFN gene expression between CLE and HV was sevenfold (p=0.016) in whole blood RNA and ninefold (p=0.002) in skin tape-derived RNA (
 online supplemental figure S3). Mean change in gene expression between CLE-A and CLE-U in skin tape-derived RNA was fourfold (p=0.010; 
 online supplemental figure S3). These data indicate that in patients presenting with active CLE skin lesions, skin tape-derived RNA may be as sensitive—perhaps even more sensitive—than blood RNA for the assessment of IFN gene signature expression.
